
// This Hyperlambda snippet uses the [execute] slot to invoke the "magic.auth.create-user" slot, creating a new user with specified attributes. It extracts the username, password, and other details from [.arguments] and assigns roles and extra information like email and name. The [else] slot ensures this operation occurs only if a preceding condition is false.
else
   execute:magic.auth.create-user
      username:x:@.arguments/*/username
      password:x:@.arguments/*/password
      is_hashed:x:@.arguments/*/is_hashed
      roles
         .:root
      extra
         email:x:@.arguments/*/email
         name:x:@.arguments/*/name
